 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A 20-minute objective win, +23 VP — you didn't out-carry them, you out-took every neutral on the map (Fangtooths and the Mini-Prime all yours, 28,117 objective damage to their 419).",
  "team": "This is the 3-stack winning the way you actually can: control the map. Every Fangtooth (min 9 and 16) and the Mini-Prime (min 17) came your way, you out-towered them 5-3, and the objective-damage gap was lopsided (28,117 vs 419). Xeebs' Khaimera anchored that with 18,352 damage to objectives and Willy's Steel frontlined (16,047 mitigated). Keep doing this — when the bot lane is even or behind, don't force fights, just keep stacking neutrals and structures.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Itemize armor against the fed physical carry: their real damage was Sparrow's 17k physical, yet only 1 of 5 of you built armor — buy an early armor piece next time and that Sparrow doesn't go 8/0.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Drongo had a rough one — 0/3/5 with hero damage 31% under your norm (520 vs 758), and the enemy Sparrow hard-carried at 8/0/0. The sim called this lane favored but the field disagrees: Drongo into Sparrow is actually a slight loss (48.6% win rate), so this wasn't on you alone — the team's objectives covered the lane. Next time, get an armor item early and play safer until you spike.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Steel did the frontline job — 5/3/1 and 16,047 damage mitigated, plus 4,025 into objectives to help the map snowball. Solid engage; just get one armor piece in against that Sparrow to make peeling the carry easier.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera was the MVP of the objective game — 3/2/3 and a massive 18,352 damage to objectives on your comfort pick (156 games, 57%), into a genuinely favored jungle matchup (53.8%). This is your lane and your win condition; keep prioritizing neutrals exactly like this."
  }
